      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/disc-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed (coarse: 1.2M cells, medium: 3.8M cells, fine: 11.4M cells). Grid convergence index (GCI) computed per Roache methodology. GCI for NIH at the medium-to-fine transition is 9.8%, exceeding the 5% threshold required at level 3. The medium mesh was selected for production runs due to computational constraints, but spatial discretization error remains insufficiently bounded for the hemolysis QoI. Achieved level 2 falls below required level 3 — this factor does NOT meet the required credibility level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions (flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM) are documented with calibrated instrumentation traceable to NIST standards. Temperature, fluid viscosity, and hematocrit are controlled and reported. Test conditions adequately replicate the intended COU operating envelope. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison metrics (mean absolute error, root-mean-square error, and Theil's inequality coefficient) computed for both NIH and pressure-head outputs. Statistical comparison framework documented. Pressure-head comparison meets acceptance threshold; NIH comparison does not. The comparison methodology itself achieves level 2 as required, even though the NIH result fails the 10% MAE criterion — the factor assesses the rigor of comparison methodology, not the pass/fail of individual results."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) are the primary QoIs directly mapped to the clinical endpoint of red blood cell damage. Secondary QoIs (pressure head, wall shear stress distribution) are also computed and correlated to hemolysis mechanisms. QoI selection is justified by published hemolysis power-law models (Giersiepen, Zhang). Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/val-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under CPB-representative flow conditions. The validation scenario shares geometry, fluid (bovine blood surrogate), flow regime (turbulent, Re ~ 8000), and hemolysis measurement protocol with the intended COU. Validation relevance is judged adequate at level 2 for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via residual norms (continuity < 1e-5, momentum < 1e-5, turbulence < 1e-4). Mass imbalance < 0.01% across all runs. Double-precision arithmetic employed throughout. Round-off and iterative errors are negligible relative to discretization error. Achieved level 2 exceeds required level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Simulation workflow executed by two independent analysts with cross-check of boundary condition assignments, material property inputs, and post-processing scripts. Discrepancies identified and resolved prior to final run. Standard operating procedure for CFD hemolysis analysis followed per internal QMS document QMS-CFD-003. Achieved level 2 exceeds required level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl2",
      "rationale": "The hemolysis power-law model (Zhang et al. 2011) is employed to relate local shear stress and exposure time to RBC damage. Model form uncertainty arises from: (1) the power-law exponent was calibrated on Couette flow data and may not generalize to impeller-dominated turbulent shear; (2) turbulence-hemolysis interaction is not explicitly modeled; (3) the k-omega SST turbulence closure under-predicts turbulent stresses in the impeller passage as evidenced by velocity profile discrepancies of 14% relative to PIV data. No alternative model form comparison (e.g., Giersiepen vs. Zhang) was performed to bound model-form uncertainty. Achieved level 2 falls below required level 3 — this factor does NOT meet the required credibility level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity assigned as Newtonian (mu = 0.0035 Pa·s) without sensitivity analysis to non-Newtonian effects. Inlet velocity profile assumed fully developed parabolic, whereas the experimental inlet condition is reported as plug flow from a peristaltic pump — this mismatch introduces inlet boundary condition uncertainty not quantified in the current submission. Geometric tolerances on impeller blade angles (±0.5°) are not propagated through the simulation. A formal uncertainty propagation study covering at least the three dominant input parameters was required at level 3 but was not performed. Achieved level 2 falls below required level 3 — this factor does NOT meet the required credibility level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements obtained from n=5 independent test runs per operating point using bovine blood from a single donor pool per run. Hematocrit controlled at 30±2%. Coefficient of variation across replicates is 8.3%, within the acceptable range for biological test samples at level 2. Sample preparation and storage protocols documented per ASTM F1841. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/equiv-inputs-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Simulation boundary conditions (flow rates, rotational speeds, fluid properties) are mapped to experimental conditions with documented traceability. Dimensional equivalency confirmed for all 5 operating points. Discrepancy in inlet velocity profile noted under Model inputs factor and assessed there. For the purposes of this factor, the mapping of experimental parameters to simulation inputs is adequately documented at level 2. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    }
